title: For Sale:   Shooting/Range Day
postcontent:
Five Stones Firearms Training LLC will be opening our range on Saturday September 19 2015 from 10am Est until 3pm Est for an afternoon of rifle and handgun shooting. The fee for the event is 25.00 per shooter. Shooters must be at least 13 years of age and all shooters under 18 must be accompanied by an adult shooter. The fee for shooters under 18 is 20.00. Admission fees must be paid prior to the shoot, if you wish to mail a check you can send it to the address listed on our contact page. This event has a limited amount of spots available.

There will be no formal training at this shoot other than a safety briefing. This shoot will allow shooters a chance to do some informal fun shooting at reactive steel targets.

We will divide the shooting time to allow for both handgun and rifle shooting.

We will furnish reactive AR 500 steel targets for the day therefore no steel core or AP ammo will be allowed this includes SS109, M855, green tip etc. Also any caliber likely to damage the steel will not be allowed. Some of these include .50BMG,.338 Lapua, .300 Win Mag, .22-250, etc. Nearly all common semi-auto, lever action, bolt action, pump action firearms will be allowed so long as they are chambered in a caliber that will  not damage our steel.  Contact us if you have any questions concerning what you would like to bring.

All shooters must wear eye and ear protection. No open toed footwear will be allowed. We advise you to wear long pants and shirts with sleeves preferably long sleeves as well as a hat.  Flying brass is hot dress accordingly. We also recommend a tarp or shooting mat as most shooting will be done on the ground.

All firing lines will be monitored by experienced range safety personal. Shooters will abide by all safety rules and will be required to sign a statement that you understand those rules; you will also be required to sign liability waivers. Failure to comply with any of the safety requirements and you will be told to leave the range.

 If you have any questions or concerns please contact us you can find contact information by clicking the contact link at the top of this page. 
http://www.fivestonesfirearmstraining.com/september-shoot.html

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ballister Molina
postcontent:
The Ballester-Molina is a pistol designed and built by the Argentine company Hispano Argentina Fábrica de Automotores SA (HAFDASA). Between 1938 and 1940, it bore the name Ballester-Rigaud. The Ballester was designed to offer the Argentine police and military a less-expensive alternative to the Sistema Colt Modelo 1927, which was itself a licensed copy of the Colt M1911A1 and built under the supervision of Colt engineers. Production of the Ballester-Molina began in 1938 and ceased in 1953. Ironically, the Sistema Colt 1927 was manufactured until 1966.[1]

The history of the company dates back to 1929, when two Spaniard entrepreneurs, Arturo Ballester and Eugenio Molina, established a branch of the Spanish Hispano-Suiza in Buenos Aires. Years later, HAFDASA hired two engineers, Frenchman Rorice Rigaud and Carlos Ballester-Molina, a relative of the founders. Rigaud became the chief designer of the firm, while Ballester-Molina was appointed chief executive officer.
There is lots of other info out there on these fine firearms, just do a bit of research. The S/N of my gun dates to between 1938-1942, all parts have matching s/n's, frame, slide & barrel. Colt is selected only because HFASADA isn't an option.

title: For Sale:  Beretta 686 Silver Pigeon I Sporting Shotgun
postcontent: At the heart of the Silver Pigeon I Sporting is the legendary 686 action, a long-standing favorite among competition shooters and hunters. Over-under actions must have a strong locking mechanism, because the stress of every shot causes the action to "want" to open. For this reason, most manufacturers place the locking lug(s) at the top of the receiver, making it strong but also taller and bulkier than it needs be. Thanks to its long experience, Beretta uses instead two conical locking lugs at mid-action, right between the barrels. This gives the 686 receiver vault-like locking strength while keeping the profile considerably lower. The advantage is that the eye of the shooter is a lot closer to the plane of his supporting hand: considerably better swing and hand-eye coordination, more targets shattered.

title: For Sale:  reduced - Rock River Arms 2-Stage National Match Trigger Kit
location: Grey Forest (NW of SA), San Antonio, Texas
postcontent:
This National Match two-stage trigger from RRA is an excellent trigger for your AR15 rifle. These are used frequently in Varmint and Long Range AR builds where a lighter 2-Stage trigger really helps accuracy and round placement. These triggers come pre-adjusted by Rock River gunsmiths as a matched pair and drop in all mil-spec lowers with no adjustment necessary for an easy drop-in install. Rock River 2-stage NM pins are .1555 in diameter and are not recommended or designed to be used with .154 pins or .170 Colt lower receivers. .1555 RRA Trigger pins will install in any standard milspec lower receiver without modification but may be noticeably more snug than the .154 pins upon install. 

This kit includes trigger, trigger spring, trigger pin, disconnector, hammer, hammer spring, and hammer pin. This 2-stage National Match trigger kit is for a lower which already has a lower parts kit installed. This does NOT include any detents, takedown pins, or other parts to complete a stripped lower.
